http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Gandhigiri-for-a-helmet/article13995902.ece

With the deadline for the helmet rule for pillion riders fast approaching, the city traffic police resorted to Gandhigiri and distributed roses and chocolates to riders without helmet today.Several teams of police have been formed across the city as part of the awareness campaign.The Electronics City traffic police, where the highest number of fatal accidents are registered, stopped bike riders without helmet and offered them roses and even gave a demo on the safety aspects of wearing a helmet.“Since the deadline has been extended to January 20, we decided to launch an awareness campaign before we start with the strict enforcement,” Electronics City Traffic Inspector Mohammed M.A. said.The K.R. Puram police have also distributed chocolates to the riders and advised them to wear helmet for safety.